Pretty much every Potbelly location is the same in terms of food, but this one excels in customer service. The eatery gets packed by the lunch rush from Northwestern, but they keep the line moving and the food coming. If there's an issue with your order, the manager quickly gets things fixed via a replacement. All of the workers are friendly as well. Food-wise, I would recommend the chicken enchilada soup paired with a turkey bacon cheddar flatbread sandwich. If they'd improve one thing, it would be adding 1 extra soup each day to get more of my favorites throughout the week, but that's a nit-picky criticism.

Staying in a hotel nearby, I passed in front of here looking for something to eat. Wasn't entirely in the mood for a sandwich at dinner, but the place was quiet and interesting enough to warrant my attention. It was just about empty, and the employee seemed slightly lackadaisical (big word!) before noticing me. The sandwiches were priced ok, I wish they offered something closer to a foot long but perhaps it's in my best interest to consume fewer calories. They toasted by default, which was fine, but I would've liked to be asked. The bread has a crispy, ciabatta-like crust and was a high point. I don't live in the vicinity of any other Potbelly's so I won't actually return often (if ever) but I would definitely do so given the chance. I'm no fan of Subway and am indifferent to Quiznos, but it is definitely above both (ironically, a Subway is across the street) and I didn't think the price was too far off either.

Used to work near this Potbelly's and came a few times a week. Love their Wreck salad, chicken salad and sometimes would stop inf or breakfast. Potbelly's has the best oatmeal chocolate chip cookies and great milkshakes!
